    <h1>Mercateo</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong><a href="https://www.mercateo.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Mercateo</a></strong> is one of the leading procurement platforms for business customers. At Mercateo, purchasers can find an extensive range in various product categories. The assortment ranges from office supplies to laboratory materials, IT and tools to hotel and gastronomy equipment (source: www.mercateo.co.uk).</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="100">1. Registering with Mercateo</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong><a href="https://www.mercateo.com/login/registercustomer?locale=en-GB&amp;geoArea=gb&amp;registration=customer&amp;state=https%253A%252F%252Fwww.mercateo.co.uk%252F%253FviewOptions%253DsecureMode.1&amp;sid3=5.147.251.210.1453969975031158" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Register</a></strong> with Mercateo to receive your access data. You will need this data for the settings in plentymarkets.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="200">2. Setting up Mercateo in plentymarkets</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Before you can set up Mercateo in plentymarkets, you need to have data for the FTP server that is to be used for the upload to Mercateo, as well as an email account for the order import.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting up Mercateo in plentymarkets:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Markets » Mercateo » Basic settings</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings as desired. Pay attention to the information given in table 1.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
