<h2 id="300">3. Setting the item availability</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Items have to be available for Mercateo. This is done in the <strong>Availability</strong> tab of an item within the <a href="/en/item/managing-items#170"><strong>Item » Edit item » Tab: Variation ID</strong></a> menu.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting the item availability for Mercateo:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Open the <strong>Item » Edit item » Open item » Tab: Variation ID » Tab: Settings</strong> menu.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the main variation in the <strong>Availability</strong> section.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Availability</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the <strong>Markets</strong> section in the selection field. <br>
→ A list with all available markets will be displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the option <strong>Mercateo</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the option <strong>Web API</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Add</strong>.<br>
→ The Market will be added.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings. <br>
→ The item is available on Mercateo.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The availability for variations can be individually edit in the <strong>Item » Edit item » Open item » Tab: Variation ID » Open variation » Tab: Availability</strong> menu.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="400">4. Exporting items and item images</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In this menu, you can export your items and item images to Mercateo.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Exporting items:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Markets » Mercateo » Data export</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Export item data</strong>.<br>
→ The item data will be exported to Mercateo.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can also export item images to Mercateo. A maximum of 100 images can be uploaded at once in JPEG format. No image will be uploaded twice.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Exporting item images:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Markets » Mercateo » Data export</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Export 100 item images:</strong>.<br>
→ The item images will be exported to Mercateo.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="500">5. Defining a sales price</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to define a sales price for the order referrer Mercateo. This price will be displayed on Mercateo.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Defining a sales price for Mercateo:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Open the menu <strong>Settings » Item » Sales price » Open sales price » Tab: Settings</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Place a checkmark next to the referrer <strong>Mercateo</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="600">6. Viewing the export history</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>An overview of exported images is displayed in this menu. The images will be displayed on different pages. 25 images can be displayed per page.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Selecting a page:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Markets » Mercateo » Export history</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select a <strong>Page</strong> from the drop-down menu.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>gear-wheel icon</strong> to display the page.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The images will be displayed along with the corresponding item ID and time of export. It is not possible to export an image more than once. However, if you want to update an image, e.g. after changes have been made to it, then click on <strong>Delete</strong> in the <strong>Release item image</strong> column. Then export this image again in the <strong>Item export</strong> menu.</p>
</div>
